In the past two decades, 128 communities have had a simple idea: to make their own school district.
To be clear, school secession isn’t a viral trend yet.
But school secession is one of the more brazen examples of affluent communities using their political clout to fence out everyone else.
With school district secession, it isn’t about moving to another place to get a district boundary between you and others.
EdBuild mistakenly counted an “ongoing” district — the Malibu School District — as “seceded.” Malibu is still currently still one district, and there have been no decisions thus far that carry any legal weight